# DAICE-specific patterns

**Authentication flow (E2E):**
```typescript
await page.goto('http://localhost:3100');
await page.getByTestId('auth-email-input').fill('test@example.com');
await page.getByTestId('auth-password-input').fill('testpass123');
await page.getByTestId('auth-login-button').click();
await expect(page.getByTestId('lobby-screen')).toBeVisible();
```

**Room creation flow:**
```typescript
await page.getByTestId('lobby-createRoom-button').click();
await page.getByTestId('roomSettings-theme-select').selectOption('High Fantasy');
await page.getByTestId('roomSettings-confirm-button').click();
await expect(page.getByTestId('room-code-display')).toBeVisible();
```

**Character creation wizard:**
```typescript
// Step 1: Class selection
await page.getByTestId('characterCreation-class-fighter').click();
await page.getByTestId('characterCreation-next-button').click();

// Step 2: Name & background
await page.getByTestId('characterCreation-name-input').fill('Thorin');
await page.getByTestId('characterCreation-next-button').click();

// Step 3: Confirmation
await page.getByTestId('characterCreation-submit-button').click();
await expect(page.getByTestId('player-list')).toContainText('Thorin');
```

**Multi-context (real-time sync testing):**
```typescript
// Context 1: Create room
const context1 = await browser.newContext();
const page1 = await context1.newPage();
await page1.goto('http://localhost:3100');
// ... login and create room, capture room code

// Context 2: Join room
const context2 = await browser.newContext();
const page2 = await context2.newPage();
await page2.goto('http://localhost:3100');
// ... login and join with room code

// Verify both see each other (Socket.IO sync)
await expect(page1.getByTestId('player-list')).toContainText('Player 2');
await expect(page2.getByTestId('player-list')).toContainText('Player 1');
```

---

# Safety & Constraints

- **Stay within allowed hosts**: localhost only (ports 3000, 3001, 3100, 3101)
- **NEVER navigate to external sites** (security risk)
- **Use Firebase emulator for auth** (never production Firebase)
- **E2E isolation**: Tests use `emulator-data-e2e` to avoid conflicts with dev
- **Self-contained tests**: Playwright config auto-starts services via webServer - no manual `yarn dev` needed

---

# Examples

**Test login flow:**
```
Use playwright. Go to http://localhost:3100, log in with test@example.com / testpass123,
assert lobby screen appears, then output e2e/auth-login.spec.ts.
```

**Verify character creation:**
```
Use playwright. Starting from lobby (localhost:3100), create a room, generate world,
then create a Fighter character named "Thorin". Confirm character appears in player list.
```

**Test real-time updates:**
```
Use playwright. Open two browser contexts. In context 1, create a room and get the code.
In context 2, join with that code. Confirm both see each other in player list (Socket.IO sync).
```

**Debug layout issue:**
```
Use playwright. Navigate to http://localhost:3100/combat, take screenshot of combat grid,
inspect if grid cells are rendering correctly at mobile viewport (375x667).
```

**Generate test file:**
```
Use playwright. Reproduce the full room creation flow (login → create room → generate world → verify room code).
Output complete e2e/room-creation-flow.spec.ts with all assertions.
```

